      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) below 5% for the primary hemolysis QoI (NIH) on a three-level mesh refinement study.",
      "rationale": "A two-level mesh refinement study was performed (coarse: 4.2 M cells; fine: 9.8 M cells). The apparent order of convergence was 1.6 and GCI for NIH was 11.4%, exceeding the 5% acceptance threshold. A third refinement level was not completed due to computational resource constraints; the team judged the 11.4% GCI acceptable given the conservative nature of the hemolysis model. Achieved level 1 (GCI > 5%) does not meet the required level 2 for this factor."
